          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Reigniting Opportunity for Innovators Act</b></p> <p>This bill amends title IV (Student Assistance) of the Higher Education Act of 1965 to make qualified founders and full-time employees of small business start-ups eligible for deferring for up to three years their loans under the federal Direct Loan program.</p> <p>If the start-up is located in an economically distressed area, qualified founders and employees are also eligible for loan cancellation of up to $20,000 under that program.</p>]]></text>
        </item>
